1. write a tcl program to find the length of the string including spaces?

set a "this is tcl scripting in physica design automation"
set b [string length $a]
puts "The length of the string is:$b"

2. write a tcl program to find the length of the string excluding white spaces?

    set text "welcome to vlsi domain in physical design engineer"
    set a [string map {" " ""} $text]
    set b [string length $a]
    puts "length of the string excluding white spaces:$b"

3. write a tcl program to find the number of the words present in string ?

     set text "welcome to vlsi domain in physical design engineer"
     foreach a $text {
     puts $a
     }
     
4. find the number of character of the text(including spaces)?

     set a "welcome to vlsi domain in physical design engineer"
     set b [string length $a]
     puts "the number of characters including space is:$b"

5. find the number of character of the text(Excluding spaces)?

      set text "This is a sample text."
      set text_nospace [string map {" " ""} $text]
      set length_nospace [string length $text_nospace]
      puts "The length of the text excluding spaces is: $length_nospace"

6. find the number of words in a text?

      set a "welcome to vlsi domain in physical design engineer"
      set i 0
      foreach b $a {
      #puts $b
      incr i
      }
      puts "the number of the words in a text is:$i"

